"{\"abstract\":\"Hatebusters is a web application for actively reporting YouTube hate speech, aiming to establish an online community of volunteer citizens. Hatebusters searches YouTube for videos with potentially hateful comments, scores their comments with a classifier trained on human-annotated data and presents users those comments with the highest probability of being hate speech. It also employs gamification elements, such as achievements and leaderboards, to drive user engagement.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"31925638\",\"name\":\"A. Anagnostou\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/31925638\"},{\"authorId\":\"51055381\",\"name\":\"Ioannis Mollas\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/51055381\"},{\"authorId\":\"2502501\",\"name\":\"Grigorios Tsoumakas\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/2502501\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[{\"arxivId\":\"2006.08328\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"51055381\",\"name\":\"Ioannis Mollas\"},{\"authorId\":\"1749884841\",\"name\":\"Zoe Chrysopoulou\"},{\"authorId\":\"1789816\",\"name\":\"Stamatis Karlos\"},{\"authorId\":\"2502501\",\"name\":\"Grigorios Tsoumakas\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[\"background\",\"methodology\"],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"1168311cb5a3e6fc1b118fa674a93286a6ffba28\",\"title\":\"ETHOS: an Online Hate Speech Detection Dataset\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/1168311cb5a3e6fc1b118fa674a93286a6ffba28\",\"venue\":\"ArXiv\",\"year\":2020},{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"1411580971\",\"name\":\"Priyam Bansal\"}],\"doi\":null,\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"b728b25daa8b0fbef927a2b8d4488aa3becaf26a\",\"title\":\"Detection of Offensive YouTube Comments, a Performance Comparison of Deep Learning Approaches\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/b728b25daa8b0fbef927a2b8d4488aa3becaf26a\",\"venue\":\"\",\"year\":2019},{\"arxivId\":\"1906.06566\",\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"5105